---
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---
<section class="philosophy" id="philosophy" aria-labelledby="philosophy-title">
  <div class="philosophy-inner">
    <p class="philosophy-eyebrow">On the design</p>
    <h2 id="philosophy-title" class="philosophy-title">By subtraction.</h2>
    <div class="philosophy-prose">
      <p>
        Lenos started as a fork of <a href="https://github.com/charmbracelet/crush">Crush</a><span class="footnote-mark">*</span>
        by Charmbracelet. We owe them the foundation. What we changed is less
        about adding and more about taking away — the tool-call layer, the
        permission management, the assumption that an AI agent needs its own
        protocol for talking to a computer.
      </p>
      <p>
        What's left is small: a model, a sandboxed shell, a transcript.
        Sandbox isolation comes for free from temenos. Multi-model support
        comes for free from speaking shell instead of tool-call JSON. Lower
        cost comes for free from fewer tokens. Each removal made the next
        one possible.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you've been frustrated by your runtime's tool-call edge cases,
        your agent's permission management, or your model's reluctance to
        run parallel tool calls — the <a href={`${base}/docs/install`}>docs</a> are a fast read.
      </p>
    </div>
    <p class="philosophy-footnote">
      <span class="footnote-mark">*</span>
      <em>λ — lenos in lowercase greek; from λῆνος, the wine-press.
      A vat where input is gathered, transformed, and refined into output.
      An old name for an old idea; we like the lineage.</em>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .philosophy {
    max-width: var(--container-marketing);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--section-gap) 1.5rem 0;
  }
  .philosophy-inner { max-width: var(--container-prose); }
  .philosophy-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-variant: small-caps;
    font-feature-settings: "smcp" 1;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--color-ink-mute);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .philosophy-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: var(--text-display-m);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }
  .philosophy-prose {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-body);
    line-height: var(--leading-prose);
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }
  .philosophy-prose p {
    margin: 0 0 1.4em;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }
  .philosophy-prose p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .philosophy-prose p:first-of-type::first-letter {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 3.6em;
    line-height: 0.85;
    float: left;
    margin: 0.05em 0.12em -0.05em 0;
    color: var(--color-brand);
  }
  .philosophy-prose em { color: var(--color-ink-soft); }
  .philosophy-prose a {
    color: var(--color-brand);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-brand);
  }
  .footnote-mark {
    font-size: 0.75em;
    vertical-align: 0.3em;
    color: var(--color-brand-gold);
    margin-left: 0.05em;
  }
  .philosophy-footnote {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: var(--text-small);
    color: var(--color-ink-mute);
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    padding-top: 1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-paper-rule);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .philosophy-footnote .footnote-mark {
    color: var(--color-brand-gold);
    margin-right: 0.4em;
  }
</style>
